package pkg

// Plan 12 gap: wellVerifiedRecursionCheck only adds edges between verified
// functions. A cycle that passes through a pure-function intermediary is
// invisible to the Tarjan SCC analysis, and pureCallTransitivelySafe does
// not detect the back-edge either.
//
// Here: verified `a` calls pure `p` in its spec; pure `p`'s body calls
// verified `a`. The cycle a -> p -> a is not detected: pureCallTransitivelySafe
// follows p's body, finds the call back to a (verified), recurses into a's
// spec, then finds the call to p (already in visited) and returns None.
// The root a is never recognised as the cycle target.
//
// This test documents the missing check. It currently FAILS because the
// expected type_error is NOT reported — the bug in plan 12 is not yet fixed.

// p: pure function whose body calls verified function a
pure
func p(n int) (ret int) {
	return a(n)
}

// a: verified function whose precondition calls pure p, completing the cycle
// This should be rejected but currently is not.
//:: ExpectedOutput(type_error)
requires p(n) > 0
ensures  ret == 1
decreases
verified
func a(n int) (ret int) {
	ret = 1
	return ret
}
